Afropop singer, Korede Bello fondly called Mr Romantic has analysed what “submission” connotes in a relationship. Educating his followers, the 25-year-old singer noted that submission in every relationship can be worded differently but still falls in two ways. According to him, agreeing to be with a partner requires submission of one’s loyalty, attention, energy, service and love.   What I do after shooting X-rated movies, by Alesh     Drums roll for Coal City film festival     AGN partners StarTimes for content production   The “Godwin” singer tweeted: “In every relationship ‘submission’ is a two way street. We just word it differently. “When you choose to be with a partner you’ve decided to submit your loyalty, attention, energy, service and love to that person. So submission is not gender sensitive” Reacting to his tweet @twistofficialmm wrote: “That’s hard, an a real matters. Only the wise can relate - Advertisement - @shakira69426966 wrote: “Ok i understand now, just new for me.” SPONSORED